{
  "texts": [
    "The occasional fluctuation of synaptic operations is caused by the variable firing rate in different models.",
    "We further test our models on extensive datasets, including two speech datasets (GSC 36 and TIMIT 37), two spiking speech datasets (SHD and SSC) 38, and two sequence datasets (S-MNIST and PS-MNIST).",
    "The experimental settings can be found in Methods and results are provided in Table 1.",
    "On these datasets, we find that our proposed DH-SNNs improve accuracy significantly over other SNNs and long short-term memory (LSTM) models even using much fewer parameters.",
    "In particular, on SHD, compared to the best reported accuracy of SNNs 33, our models can improve accuracy from 90.4% to 92.1% with only 36% parameters; on SSC, our models boost the best reported accuracy from 74.2% to 82.46% with only 45% parameters."
  ]
}